<http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> <https://w3id.org/emmo/application/datadoc#conformance> "ddoc:mandatory" .
# 
# http://purl.org/dc/terms/identifier
<http://purl.org/dc/terms/identifier> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#AnnotationProperty> .
<http://purl.org/dc/terms/identifier> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "URI or other unique identifier of the resource being described." .
<http://purl.org/dc/terms/identifier> <http://purl.org/vocab/vann/usageNote> "Recommended practice is to identify the resource by means of a string conforming to an identification system. Examples include International Standard Book Number (ISBN), Digital Object Identifier (DOI), and Uniform Resource Name (URN).  Persistent identifiers should be provided as HTTP URIs." .
<http://purl.org/dc/terms/identifier> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> "foaf:Agent" .
<http://purl.org/dc/terms/identifier> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "identifier" .
<http://purl.org/dc/terms/identifier> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#theme> "ddoc:datadoc" .
<http://purl.org/dc/terms/identifier> <https://w3id.org/emmo/application/datadoc#conformance> "ddoc:optional" .
